This paper discusses privacy-preserving recommender systems, which are commonly studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel approach to improve the accuracy of these systems, which involves probabilistic techniques and partitioning, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG), database (cs.DB), and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CR and cs.IR, followed by cs.LG, cs.DB, and cs.SI.
